Facelock authselect profile for Fedora/RHEL.

Based on the default sssd profile with optional facelock face authentication.

Usage:
  sudo authselect select facelock with-facelock

Features:
  with-facelock    Enable face authentication via pam_facelock.so

This profile adds pam_facelock.so as a sufficient auth method before
password authentication. If face recognition fails or is unavailable,
authentication falls through to the standard password prompt.

Requirements:
  - facelock package installed
  - At least one face enrolled: facelock enroll
  - facelock daemon running: systemctl enable --now facelock-daemon
